The paper deals with interval temporal logics, which are a subfield of logic and computer science. The paper discusses the decidability of different fragments of Halpern and Shoham's HS logic, which is a well-known interval temporal logic. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on the logical aspects of interval temporal logics, cs.LO is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because the paper deals with decision procedures and complexity analysis, which are important topics in AI, data structures and algorithms, programming languages, and machine learning.
